lay_data"},{"data":{"text/html":["<pre style=\"white-space:pre;overflow-x:auto;line-height:normal;font-family:Menlo,'DejaVu Sans Mono',consolas,'Courier New',monospace\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold\"> Trainable params: </span><span style=\"color: #00af00; text-decoration-color: #00af00\">61,706</span> (241.04 KB)\n","</pre>\n"],"text/plain":["\u001b[1m Trainable params: \u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;34m61,706\u001b[0m (241.04 KB)\n"]},"metadata":{},"output_type":"display_data"},{"data":{"text/html":["<pre style=\"white-space:pre;overflow-x:auto;line-height:normal;font-family:Menlo,'DejaVu Sans Mono',consolas,'Courier New',monospace\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold\"> Non-trainable params: </span><span style=\"color: #00af00; text-decoration-color: #00af00\">0</span> (0.00 B)\n","</pre>\n"],"text/plain":["\u001b[1m Non-trainable params: \u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;34m0\u001b[0m (0.00 B)\n"]},"metadata":{},"output_type":"display_data"}],"source":["from tensorflow.keras.models import Sequential\n","from tensorflow.keras.layers import Input, Conv2D, AveragePooling2D, Flatten, Dense\n","\n","model = Sequential([\n","\n","    Input(shape=(32, 32, 1)),\n","\n","    # C1\n","    Conv2D(filters=6, kernel_size=(5,5), activation='tanh'),\n","\n","    # S2\n","    AveragePooling2D(pool_size=(2,2)),\n","\n","    # C3\n","    Conv2D(filters=16, kernel_size=(5,5), activation='tanh'),\n","\n","    # S4\n","    AveragePooling2D(pool_size=(2,2)),\n","\n","    # C5\n","    Conv2D(filters=120, kernel_size=(5,5), activation='tanh'),\n","\n","    Flatten(),\n","\n","    # F6\n","    Dense(84, activation='tanh'),\n","\n","    # Output\n","    Dense(10, activation='softmax')\n","])\n","\n","model.compile(\n","    optimizer='adam',\n","    loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy',\n","    metrics=['accuracy']\n",")\n","\n","model.summary()"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":10,"id":"d1b0602a","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.execute_input":"2026-05-26T18:56:28.693579Z","iopub.status.busy":"2026-05-26T18:56:28.692652Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-05-26T18:56:28.696772Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-05-26T18:56:28.695874Z"},"papermill":{"duration":0.015227,"end_time":"2026-05-26T18:56:28.698425+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-05-26T18:56:28.683198+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"outputs":[],"source":["# history = model.fit(\n","#     x_train, y_train,\n","#     epochs=3,\n","#     batch_size=128,\n","#     validation_split=0.1\n","# )"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":11,"id":"196cdb98","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.execute_input":"2026-05-26T18:56:28.716393Z","iopub.status.busy":"2026-05-26T18:56:28.715637Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-05-26T18:56:28.71949Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-05-26T18:56:28.718748Z"},"papermill":{"duration":0.014592,"end_time":"2026-05-26T18:56:28.721101+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-05-26T18:56:28.706509+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"outputs":[],"source":["# test_loss, test_acc = model.evaluate(x_test, y_test)"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"d572b287","metadata":{"papermill":{"duration":0.008332,"end_time":"2026-05-26T18:56:28.737735+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-05-26T18:56:28.729403+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"source":["## Charecterstics\n","\n","### Advantages\n","\n","| Advantage               | Explanation            |\n","| ----------------------- | ---------------------- |\n","| Simple architecture     | Easy to understand     |\n","| Efficient               | Fewer parameters       |\n","| Good for small datasets | Works well on MNIST    |\n","| Foundation of CNNs      | Inspired future models |\n","\n","### Limitations\n","\n","| Limitation                      | Explanation                       |\n","| ------------------------------- | --------------------------------- |\n","| Small network                   | Cannot handle very complex images |\n","| Low accuracy on modern datasets | Weak for large-scale vision tasks |\n","| Uses tanh                       | Slower than ReLU                  |\n","\n","### LeNet vs Modern CNNs\n","\n","| Feature    | LeNet   | Modern CNNs       |\n","| ---------- | ------- | ----------------- |\n","| Depth      | Shallow | Very deep         |\n","| Parameters | Small   | Millions          |\n","| Dataset    | MNIST   | ImageNet and more |\n","| Activation | Tanh    | ReLU              |\n","| Pooling    | Average | Max pooling       |\n","\n","# AlexNet\n","\n","AlexNet is one of the most influential deep learning models in computer vision history. It was introduced in 2012 by:\n","\n","* Alex Krizhevsky\n","* Ilya Sutskever\n","* Geoffrey Hinton\n","\n","AlexNet won the famous ImageNet Large Scale Visual Recognition Challenge 2012 with a huge improvement over previous methods.\n","\n","**Legacy of AlexNet**\n","\n","AlexNet inspired modern CNN architectures:\n","\n","* VGGNet\n","* GoogLeNet\n","* ResNet\n","\n","It proved deep learning could outperform traditional computer vision methods on large-scale tasks.\n","\n","## Why AlexNet Was Revolutionary\n","\n","Before AlexNet:\n","\n","* Traditional computer vision relied heavily on manual feature engineering.\n","* Deep neural networks were difficult to train effectively.\n","* GPUs were not commonly used for deep learning.\n","\n","AlexNet changed this by introducing:\n","\n","| Innovation            | Impact                  |\n","| --------------------- | ----------------------- |\n","| Deep CNN architecture | Better feature learning |\n","| ReLU activation       | Faster training         |\n","| GPU training          | Massive speedup         |\n","| Dropout               | Reduced overfitting     |\n","| Data augmentation     | Better generalization   |\n","\n","This triggered the modern deep learning revolution.\n","\n","## Main Goal of AlexNet\n","\n","AlexNet was designed for large-scale image classification.\n","\n","Input image example:\n","\n","* dog\n","* car\n","* airplane\n","* cat\n","\n","Output: Predicted object category.\n","\n","**ImageNet Dataset**\n","\n","AlexNet was trained on ImageNet. It contains:\n","\n","* Over 1 million training images\n","* 1000 object categories\n","\n","Examples:\n","\n","* cats\n","* dogs\n","* birds\n","* vehicles\n","* furniture\n","\n","## AlexNet Architecture\n","\n","| Layer  | Name                | Type                   | Kernel / Pool     | Stride | Output Size | Activation | Parameters | Purpose                                     |\n","| ------ | ------------------- | ---------------------- | ----------------- | ------ | ----------- | ---------- | ---------- | ------------------------------------------- |\n","| Input  | Input Image         | —                      | —                 | —      | 227×227×3   | —          | 0          | RGB image input                             |\n","| C1     | Convolution         | Conv                   | 11×11, 96 filters | 4      | 55×55×96    | ReLU       | 34,944     | Large-scale edge + color feature extraction |\n","| S1     | Pooling             | Max Pool (overlapping) | 3×3               | 2      | 27×27×96    | —          | 0          | Downsampling + translation invariance       |\n","| LRN1   | Local Response Norm | —                      | —                 | —      | 27×27×96    | —          | 0          | Normalization + neuron competition          |\n","| C2     | Convolution         | Conv (grouped)         | 5×5, 256 filters  | 1      | 27×27×256   | ReLU       | 614,656    | Texture + mid-level features                |\n","| S2     | Pooling             | Max Pool (overlapping) | 3×3               | 2      | 13×13×256   | —          | 0          | Spatial reduction                           |\n","| LRN2   | Local Response Norm | —                      | —                 | —      | 13×13×256   | —          | 0          | Stabilization + generalization              |\n","| C3     | Convolution         | Conv                   | 3×3, 384 filters  | 1      | 13×13×384   | ReLU       | 885,120    | Complex feature extraction                  |\n","| C4     | Convolution         | Conv (grouped)         | 3×3, 384 filters  | 1      | 13×13×384   | ReLU       | 1,327,488  | Object part refinement                      |\n","| C5     | Convolution         | Conv (grouped)         | 3×3, 256 filters  | 1      | 13×13×256   | ReLU       | 884,992    | High-level object representation            |\n","| S5     | Pooling             | Max Pool (overlapping) | 3×3               | 2      | 6×6×256     | —          | 0          | Final spatial compression                   |\n","| F6     | Fully Connected     | Dense                  | —                 | —      | 4096        | ReLU       | 37,752,832 | Global feature reasoning                    |\n","| D6     | Dropout             | Regularization         | —                 | —      | 4096        | —          | 0          | Prevent overfitting (p=0.5)                 |\n","| F7     | Fully Connected     | Dense                  | —                 | —      | 4096        | ReLU       | 16,781,312 | Deep feature abstraction                    |\n","| D7     | Dropout             | Regularization         | —                 | —      | 4096        | —          | 0          | Prevent overfitting (p=0.5)                 |\n","| Output | Classification      | Softmax                | —                 | —      | 1000        | Softmax    | 4,097,000  | Final class probabilities                   |\n","\n","![CNN Architecture](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/masum184e/handbook-old/removed/images/cnn/alexnet.png)\n","\n","### Input Layer\n","\n","AlexNet takes **RGB images**:\n","\n","$$\n","227 \\times 227 \\times 3\n","$$\n","\n","Unlike LeNet (grayscale), AlexNet learns from:\n","\n","* color information (RGB channels)\n","* large-scale natural images (ImageNet dataset)\n","\n","### First Convolution Layer (C1)\n","\n","**Configuration**\n","\n","* 96 filters\n","* Kernel: ($11 \\times 11$)\n","* Stride: 4 (large stride for fast downsampling)\n","\n","**What it learns**\n","\n","* simple edges\n","* color blobs\n","* basic texture patterns\n","\n","This layer aggressively reduces spatial resolution early.\n","\n","### Activation Function\n","\n","AlexNet popularized the use of **ReLU (Rectified Linear Unit)**\n","\n","**Why ReLU was important**\n","\n","Earlier CNNs used:\n","\n","* sigmoid\n","* tanh\n","\n","Problems:\n","\n","* slow convergence\n","* vanishing gradients\n","\n","ReLU solved these by:\n","\n","* faster training\n","* sparse activations\n","* better gradient flow\n","\n","### Pooling Layer (S1)\n","\n","* Max pooling ($3 \\times 3$), stride 2\n","\n","**Purpose**\n","\n","* reduces computation\n","* improves translation invariance\n","* retains strongest activations\n","\n","### Local Response Normalization (LRN1 & LRN2)\n","\n","AlexNet introduced **Local Response Normalization**\n","\n","**Purpose:**\n","\n","* encourages competition between adjacent neurons\n","* improves generalization\n","* stabilizes early training\n","\n","Modern CNNs usually replace LRN with **Batch Normalization**\n","\n","### Middle Convolution Layers (C2–C5)\n","\n","These layers form the **core feature hierarchy**:\n","\n","#### C2\n","\n","* 256 filters (grouped convolution in original paper)\n","* learns:\n","  * textures\n","  * repeated patterns\n","  * simple object parts\n","\n","#### C3\n","\n","* 384 filters\n","* learns:\n","  * combinations of textures\n","  * edges forming shapes\n","  * mid-level patterns\n","\n","#### C4 (Grouped Convolution)\n","\n","* 384 filters\n","* learns:\n","  * object parts\n","  * structured patterns\n","  * more complex compositions\n","\n","#### C5 (Grouped Convolution)\n","\n","* 256 filters\n","* produces:\n","  * full object-level representations\n","  * high-level spatial features\n","\n","> Features evolve from **edges → textures → parts → objects**\n","\n","##### Grouped Convolution\n","\n","AlexNet used **2 GPUs**, so some layers were split into groups.\n","\n","**Benefits:**\n","\n","* parallel computation\n","* reduced memory usage\n","* enabled training large CNNs in 2012\n","\n","### Pooling Layers (S5)\n","\n","* Max pooling ($3 \\times 3$), stride 2\n","* reduces feature map to 6×6×256\n","\n","**Purpose of pooling:**\n","\n","* downsampling\n","* translation invariance\n","* feature compression before FC layers\n","\n","### Dropout Layers (after F6 and F7)\n","\n","AlexNet uses dropout for regularization:\n","\n","#### D6 (after F6)\n","\n","* randomly drops 50% of neurons\n","* prevents overfitting\n","\n","#### D7 (after F7)\n","\n","* further regularization\n","* improves generalization\n","\n","### Fully Connected Layers (F6 & F7)\n","\n","#### F6\n","\n","* 4096 neurons\n","* converts spatial features into global representation\n","\n","#### F7\n","\n","* 4096 neurons\n","* refines class-discriminative features\n","\n","These layers contain the **majority of parameters (~95%)**.\n","\n","### Output Layer\n","\n","* 1000 classes (ImageNet dataset)\n","* activation: **Softmax**\n","\n","$$\n","P(class_i) = \\frac{e^{z_i}}{\\sum_j e^{z_j}}\n","$$\n","\n","The output layer:\n","\n","* converts logits into probability distribution\n","* assigns probability to each of the 1000 object categories\n","* final prediction = class with highest probability"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":12,"id":"a2f59507","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.execute_input":"2026-05-26T18:56:28.756712Z","iopub.status.busy":"2026-05-26T18:56:28.755895Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-05-26T18:56:53.184672Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-05-26T18:56:53.183631Z"},"papermill":{"duration":24.440788,"end_time":"2026-05-26T18:56:53.186631+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-05-26T18:56:28.745843+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","output_type":"stream","text":["Downloading data from https://www.cs.toronto.edu/~kriz/cifar-10-python.tar.gz\n","\u001b[1m170498071/1